2. Definitions

"The Software" means the DevTools codebase and associated
documentation that is distributed under this license, including any
portion of it.

"The Licensor" means the DevTools Contributors who hold copyright in
the Software.

"You" means the individual or entity accepting this license.

"Your Company" means any legal entity, sole proprietorship, or other
organization that you work for, plus any entity that controls, is
controlled by, or is under common control with that organization.

"Internal Business Use" means use of the Software by you or Your
Company solely for your own workflows and operations, without offering
the Software itself, or any service whose primary value is the
Software, to third parties.

"Non-Commercial / Personal Use" means use of the Software by an
individual for private purposes where no one is paying for access to
the Software or to a service whose primary value is the Software.

"Commercial Redistribution" means distributing the Software, or a
derivative of the Software, or providing access to it, as a product or
service for which you or Your Company receive a fee or other monetary
compensation, where the primary value of what is being sold is the
Software's functionality.

