4. Limitations (No SaaS, No Resale)

You may NOT engage in Commercial Redistribution of the Software unless
you have a separate written commercial license from the Licensor.

In particular, without such a commercial license, you may NOT:

- sell the Software or any modified version of it as a product;
- license, rent, lease, or otherwise charge a fee specifically for
  access to the Software;
- offer the Software, or any modified version of it, as a hosted,
  managed, or "software as a service" product where the Software (or a
  derivative of it) is a primary component of the paid offering;
- distribute binaries or hosted instances of the Software to third
  parties for a fee where the core value arises substantially from the
  Software's functionality.

Using the Software as a tool in your own business, including for
paid consulting, development, or operational services, is allowed as
long as:

- you are not providing the Software itself (or a rebranded version)
  to your customers; and
- your customers are paying you for your services, not for access to
  DevTools as a product.

